{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "18", "S": "19"}}, "news": [{"title": "Whitestone REIT to be taken private by Ares in $1.7 billion deal", "para": "Ares Management will buy Whitestone REIT in a $1.7 billion all-cash deal.  Whitestone shareholders will receive $19 per share.  This acquisition follows months of takeover interest and shareholder pressure.  The deal is expected to close in the third quarter of 2026.  The transaction has received unanimous board approval.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/whitestone-reit-to-be-taken-private-by-ares-in-1-7-billion-deal/130147110?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-48612/130147110.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "international"}, {"title": "Traders oppose RMC crackdown on commercial activities in Jharkhand Housing Board colonies", "para": "Traders in Jharkhand State Housing Board colonies are protesting against the Ranchi Municipal Corporation's move to shut down commercial activities in residential areas.  Despite JSHB's stance on these being strictly residential zones, shopkeepers fear losing their livelihoods.  The Chamber of Commerce questions the issuance of trade licenses if the areas are non-commercial, demanding viable alternatives and rehabilitation before any evictions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/retail/traders-rally-against-rmcs-crackdown-on-commercial-activities-in-jharkhand-housing-board-colonies/130147481?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22750/130147481.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "retail"}, {"title": "DDA conducts demolition drive in south Delhi's Sainik Farm", "para": "The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) conducted a demolition drive in the Sainik Farm area of south Delhi, targeting two residential plots. Residents alleged the action was illegal, claiming a court stay order was ignored and questioning the DDA's land demarcation. This comes as the government plans to regularize unauthorized colonies.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/dda-demolition-drive-sparks-controversy-in-sainik-farm-south-delhi/130147015?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-247033/130147015.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}